place_description:
Tastes of Greece
Breakfast, lunch, and dinner
Music, Bar, and events

reviews_data.review_text: The lamb gyro was probably one of the better ones we have had anywhere

Wow. Real authentic Greek food made with real  Extra Olive Oil. Gyro were generous, and Pita was soft like homemade. Hummus was so good. It's amazing how good hummus tastes without canola or sunflower oil. Friendly attentive staff. Best Baklava ever. Can't say enough good. Looking forward to the next visit.
I love that this is one of few places I can still get Galaktoboureko or Bougatsa in Charlotte. Not enough Greek places have these on their menu. And the Spanakopita is pretty good too

I tried this restaurant for the first time. I ordered the classic gyro, which has fries in it. I love gyros. Although it wasn't my favorite with the fries in the gyro it tasted good. The homemade tzatziki sauce was really good. I got the hummus as a side which also had a great taste. I bought the baklava for my fiance which she thought it was good but very sweet. I gave the atmosphere a 4 only because it was empty and I ordered to go. Overall the food is good and I will go there again. Do go and try it for yourselves though and I'm sure you'll also leave there satisfied with your food.
Gyro, spanakopita, bacon egg and cheese and coffee were all incredible. Will definitely be back soon.

Local family owned and definitely worth a visit.  We are from out of town or we would be regulars.  Went for breakfast both food and coffee were excellent.  Very good breakfast sandwiches and recommend the ham and cheese pie.
I've been to Greece and this place does not disappoint.  The gyros and baclava are on point.  A true gem.

Wasn't sure what to expect. We wanted Greek food and decided to try an app and dessert before we decided we wanted dinner from there.

Hummus was ok n pita bread was warmed up and not fresh . Baklava cheesecake was 4/10 did not taste like cheesecake at all.graham crumble is not needed
10/10 food, 10/10 vibes, 10/10 service. love it & definitely coming back!
Great little authentic Greek restaurant.   We will definitely be back.
10/10 hidden gem. Great food, drinks and deserts. Authentic Greek food and vibes, can't recommend enough. The staff are all extremely nice as well.

Went in the other night for the first time to get a pastry. The owner was there and we chatted for a bit and he kindly gave me some free deserts to try out, everything was amazing. I ordered to-go lunch today and it was the best greek food in charlotte hands down! Definitely one of my new favorite spots!

Love this little hidden gem.

The staff here is always friendly.

Their food is great. The lamb gyro & especially their homemade tzaziki sauce is so good.

I know once these apartments across the street get built this place will be slapping!
everyone is so nice the food is great and authentic! i haven't had anything bad, full bar! pitas a great and the spanopita is my fav so flaky, there's outdoor seating
First time here.  Attended a party.  Didn't have any food, but was told by friends, the lemon pepper wings were great!
Amazing food. We had pizza, a gyro, lemon pepper chicken, Greek salad, and hummus. Everything single item was next level delicious. We will be coming back next time we find ourselves in Charlotte.

Freddo Cappuccinos were perfect. We had breakfast and some desserts and loved everything. Wonderful people at the restaurant which had a very cute Greek island look with bougainvillea and  blue accents.
Wonderful food, delicious coffee and friendly staff. They've started doing karaoke on Friday nights. Will be coming back again.

Amazing spot, walked in with multiple groups of people chatting, some in Greek, and having a good time. The waitress was kind and very helpful. Best Pita I've had since being Greece. Will absolutely be coming back!

I'm a sucker for a good Greek restaurant/bakery so I had to stop in here. I ordered a ham and cheese pie, kokakia, and a cappuccino. The pie was flakey and the subtle sweetness from the powdered sugar paired well with the saltiness of the cheese and ham. The kokakia was a tasty little treat and the cappuccino hit the spot. Good atmosphere and super respectful service. I would happily come back here!

Such a fun spot. If you are looking for authentic Greek coffee and pastries, this is your spot. I love visiting and hearing all of the spirited conversations in Greek while enjoying a delicious baklava. Definitely a hidden gem
Gyros, hummus and vibe.
I had a great time at Mocco Bistro, the food is on point, beer is cold and the employees are very warm and welcoming. Must check it out. I had the lamb gyro
Very tasty and super relaxed atmosphere.   The service was very friendly and the food was great.
Very nice & welcoming gentlemen working here, I tried the cheesecake baklava it was amazing. I will definitely be back to try more.. I highly recommend you stop by!
Excelente me gusta.

I got a refreshing cucumber long island which was tasty and a salmon pita wrap. The baklava cheesecake was so yummy too. They had complementary water and we sat out on the benches since the weather was nice.

The food was gross. Period. Cucumbers were old and I didn't eat them for fear of stomach ache. Chicken seemed microwaved the fries were tasteless and had a weird texture, like food lion brand frozen fries. I think this is a great place for dessert and coffee. I do not recommend lunch super over priced for quality of food.
Great service. Super fresh ingredients on the Gyro which was awesome. Really cute and fairly priced date night or lunch!
I'm from out of town and was recommended to try Mocco Bistro out. The food was amazing! Very delicious and fresh. I definitely recommend everyone checks it out! You cannot go wrong eating here.
Great service here every time and great coffee and pastries that you can't find in most other coffee shops.
Still the best and most underrated coffee in Charlotte. Get the Freddy Cappuccino and cheese pie (or custard pie - just get BOTH!)
love this spot! cute little patio. great for coffee, breakfast, lunch, catering! desserts are amazing. the owners are awesome!!

The frappe is horrible. Too much caffeine. Little to no milk/ice cream. It felt like I was drinking a double espresso with ice. This is simply not how a frappe should be done. You don't add ice in a frappe, you blend it in. AND you add milk/ice cream. $6 wasted.

The place itself seems nice and cozy.
Took my kids there this morning, first time there.... food and pastrys was all soo delicious! Gyro Pita with French Fries for $11.95 was enough to feed 2.
Amazing spot I love it here
Been going here for awhile and always friendly, good coffee and pastries!

Reasonable prices. The baklava and fredo cappuccino are great! Inside is clean with relaxing music and nice pictures. Nice little patio to get some sun...it is near a busy road but it's not too loud. Service is ok.

I can only speak for the desserts, but I didn't care for what I got. The one on the left had that cooler taste that resembled the smell of the restaurant. Despite that, it was clean and customer service was fine. I'd probably come again to give the food a shot.
Perfect bistro, my new favorite place for breakfast. Kind staff, delicious food & coffee and it's even affordable... what's not to love?

Easily the best baklava in Charlotte, and they make two sizes, small and large. Honestly some of the best baklava I've ever had. If you can't tell I'm obsessed with baklava. But this place is great, tons of delicious items and the prices are fantastic. Very authentic flavors and great quality food.
Tasty desserts, nice prices, but poor coffee. No barista here :(

Lovely, quaint breakfast spot with delicious coffee! We tried cheese and spinach pies and a sausage and cheese croissant for a brunch type meal. Portions were generous, and staff very helpful. Parking adequate, nice street side outdoor seating and fully accessible!

We moved around the corner from this place about 18 months ago and every time I drive past I kick myself for not remembering to go for breakfast. Well we finally went and I'm so glad I did. This place is cute, the staff is friendly, and our food was delicious. My wife and I both got the sausage egg and cheese on a croissant. I'm about halfway through mine and was moved to write this review. So happy we went, we will be back!
Everything I've had here has been super delicious and authentic. They are also very kind which always makes it a pleasure to stop in and grab my favorites :)
Love this place! The staff is friendly and most everything there is good - my favorites are the spinach pie, dolmades, and their espresso.
Love this place!  All the Greek food and pastries are just delicious!  I'm a regular there--I must get a spanakopita there weekly! Ever try their hot dogs? They're fantastic, too.
Everything is delicious and the neighborhood is enticing too.

The breakfast sandwiches here are unmatched! The value and taste are on point. You need to try them out. The coffee is unbeatable too - do yourself a favor and try the mochacchino!

Friendliest employees ever too!
Live around the corner and finally got a chance to pop in, will definitely come back I'm excited to explore the menu

Amazing atmosphere and delicious food!!! First time coming here and I was not disappointed. I will be coming back again. The coffee was perfect and the croissant I had made me text everyone in my phone to come and get one. If they don't then that's on them

Great bakery!  I visit it at least weekly.       Excellent place to convene for a work meeting, or with a friend.  If you are in LoSo or anywhere on South Blvd, go and check them out.  I think you will enjoy as much as I do.
Delicious food and amazing experience.  I am obsessed with grape leaves!!! These are delicious.
This place is great. My second time here while visiting Charlotte. The Napoleon is unbelievable and the spinach feta pastry is terrific. Super friendly staff too. I love their Greek authenticity!
Had the cheese pie, it was delicious, the koulourakia, Ekmek dessert and Milfay/ Napoleon was to die for!
Great customer service
Rude service from female server behind counter to the left that passes out to go orders. She was texting and extremely unprofessional, will never go back to Mocco again!
Delicious breakfast and organic coffee! A great local spot.
The best coffee and deserts place in charlotte... Phrento phrape kai gluka phantastika...!!! Kai polu kalo phai!!!
The food is absolutely INCREDIBLE! Sweet or savory, you have so many delicious options. The staff is very friendly as well. I'm upset that I just found this place. I'm about to become a regular! :)

Terrible coffee. The milk in my coffee had small chunks in it. They also use artificial syrups that are near inedible, not only that but it was super expensive. 17 dollars for two coffees and a muffin?
All the food we had was delicious!
Great bougatsa!!
I had a cappuccino and it's taste really good  and had a delicious apricot cookie.
Been here a few times now when going towards the city.. Easily the best sausage egg and she's bagel I've ever had. The coffee is also excellent and I like the vibe
Best pies ever!!!! Best coffee!!!!
This is a sweet little spot. Good coffee and brunch/breakfast at a very reasonable price
Great coffee and breakfast sandwiches!!  My go-to place.
Great place to meet with your friend or client
This place is amazing!!! Spanakopita is the best I've had, and everyone who works here is really friendly. Do yourself a favor and check it out!
Delicious breakfast sandwich and latte! Fast and friendly service. Comfortable and quiet enough to work from here.
Heavenly Cheese pie and coffee!!!  Best way to start my day!!
Amazing! Every time I've been- they have been absolutely the most friendly crew, and the food and coffee is some of the best I've had in south end for a cafe! Go give it a try!

I just had my best lunch out for 2021.
And brought home some home made pastry to boot.
You will not do better.   The capachino is supurb as well.

Really good coffee and really good breakfast sandwiches. Both are very high quality and the biscuit breakfast sandwich I got was huge. The prices are really good, much less than Sbucks or the "hipster" coffee shops. I'll definitely be back.

Stopped in for a to go coffee since Mocco's is solo close to home. Got a hazelnut latte very quickly from a lovely barista! Cute inside-many folks enjoying the indoor area (seating outside too). Coffee was less strong/intense than St....ks which I prefer. I also preferred the $1.45 lower pricccce. Parking lot is manuverable; but it's worth it! Better taste for less. (seems best to arrive to Mocco's parking lot from the south (S. Blvd) and turn left to enter.

Best SEC sandwich in South End(Saysage patty on the top and bottom with egg and cheese in the middle- its huge)!!! Tremendous family run business that I will now be back to dozens of times. Mom and Daughter work their butts off. Cappuccino was made with love!
Tasty food, great service, good coffee, awesome prices. What more could we ask for?
Cozy, little place perfect to enjoy a coffee and some delicious European desserts with family and friends.

The best place ever!
It is my 5
Home made desserts! The staff is very friendly and helpful. Also the passion fruit italian soda was delicious!
Everything was so good
Sensational.
Excellent place
The best pastry in Charlotte
Awesome service. Thanks Tyler.
Great coffee shop with fresh Greek deserts and more!
Love this place.  Great place to drink coffee and surf the internet.

You don't find too many Greek places that make their own pastries and breads and snacks like in Greece and they do not get them from tarpon springs.
Fresh, yummy, get it!
The best cappuccino I've had.
Great coffee, great food, great place!!!!!
Good
Nice atmosphere, delicious deserts,  very kind host
High quality pastery choices. Coffee quality is fantastic. The daily special was Gyro the day I visited.
Delicious breakfast and Greek traditional dessert! Must try. Hidden gem in Lower Southend. Super friendly staff.
Coffee is delicious and the food is good!
Getting pastries from there is like having "Greece in a box"! Authentic and fresh!

Wow!  This place was a welcome surprise.  Everything was on point.  Chicken Souvlaki was the best I have ever had, and I have had many.  Baklava was perfect too.  This is a well kept secret!  Highly recommend!
The most authentic Greek cafe in Charlotte!
Pulled up at 9:15pm and this place was closed. Shows closing time at 10pm.

I wish I had started going there when I first saw it. It is extremely clean, comfortable atmosphere, phenomenal food, and reasonably priced for the quality of what you get.  The pastries are home made on the premise. The people that work there are very personable also.
Fast service, great food
I went there to try the Ekmek Kataifi for the first time. It did not disappoint!! It was delicious! I plan on going back sometime to order another piece.

Food selection is small but has great range and high quality. Baked goods are excellent and made fresh daily. Delicious, nutty coffee, and even a bar. Excellent ambience and music choice. Great place for all times of day and occasions.
Family owned spot with great service, fresh coffee, and amazing baked goods! Hello giant napoleans!
Excellent
Awesome spot- I've driven past it for years but never checked it out. So glad I finally visited. Neat atmosphere.

The owner's mom is the pastry chef and had made the best tiramisu I've had besides Vincent's in NYC. BEST EVER IN CHARLOTTE!!!
We had 6 desserts and were asked which we loved the most, everything we had was fantastic however I am writing the review 2 months later and the tiramisu was epic enough to remember! Keep baking with  love, because we all benefit.
Quiet.  Friendly and have a good coffee.  His  tender Fabrizio very educated and gentleman
Love it here! Fantastic coffee, great authentic Greek/Mediterranean snacks and desserts too!
Great service! Their homemade cheese and ham croissant was heavenly. Worth the stop, would go again if in town.
Great coffee and pastries.

Fantastic. The napoleon is a must and you get so much for the value. Great spot to take someone on a date. The ice tea was really good too.
I cant say enough good things about this place
Nice place to stop for a quick bite. Patio area is also pet friendly.  Parking was a little confusing but overall is good!
This place is good value, the coffee is great. Also they have a variety of desserts and typical Greek products. Don't miss the Tiramisu it is delicious!
Great coffee, great food and great staff.
I liked it. Good atmosphere and kind service.
Only place I'd go out of my way to get coffee is here! Labrini definitely knows how to make some good coffee!
Good coffee and desserts
Really good pastries.

First time going here and I'll definitely be back to try more desserts. I tried cheesecake baklava which tasted even better when refrigerated, baklava and napoleon. I like both the cheesecake baklava and baklava, but I'm not fond of napoleon. I like that the napoleon is not too sweet but the whipped cream is a little bit overwhelming. Nonetheless, the staff are friendly and it is a great place to even hang out.
Favorite spot to stop on Friday mornings for coffee.

Delightful oasis of a cafe off south Blvd near intersection of old Pineville road. The BEST spanakopita fresh out of the oven every hour of the day. Delicious pastries baked onsite. Full coffee bar and drinks as well. My best lunch break when I get to come here. Friendly service. Fresh delicious food. Can't go wrong here. YUM! One of my favorite restaurants in Charlotte!
They have a delicious dessert
Finally a place in Charlotte where you can enjoy a freddo!
Tasty pastries.
Delicious Greek pastries. Flaky and light! Great coffee.
Good coffee and breakfast
Fantastic little deserts and coffee! Friendly staff and well priced!
Love this place. Basically my second home. Best Fredo cappuccino. And yummy waffles!!!

Stopped by when I was in Charlotte with my wife. Excellent Greek style napoleon and another dessert the name of which I can't remember. It was a very light spongy texture with cream on top and a thin filo dough type crust. Good strong coffee. Great service.
The best freddo!

I almost never review places but I just had to for this place. Someone got me baklava from here for my birthday and I just have to say it's probably the best I've had, which is saying a lot because I have had a LOT of great baklava. Will definitely be coming in to get some myself soon.
We were in town for a marriage conference and looked up "best desserts in Charlotte" and this bakery came up.  We drove the 2 miles and ordered 4 different desserts.  Wonderful sweets and management!
Baklava cheesecake was AMAZING
Great food and great service. If you're looking for a taste of Europe here in Charlotte, then this is the place.

I thoroughly enjoyed the strawberry cheesecake and got chocolate that I had, and my boyfriend was really impressed with his tiramisu! You can tell they care about their products and the environment - it's a really nice place and a great place for some indulgent  treats.
The most amazing spinach and feta pie, great coffee and friendly service. A true European/Greek cafe vibe that creates a relaxed atmosphere.
Great coffee,  friendly staff and amazing food!  I try and go every morning before work!
Every pastry I have had here was really delicious.  I particular like their napoleon; it is my favorite napoleon in Charlotte.  The coffee was okay, but nothing special.
Great food and drinks, awesome hospitality!
It's delicious ... me encanto
Organic desserts and organic coffee...
Best Desserts and Coffee, Greek Style!
Overall the best coffee shop I've been to in Charlotte.
The greatest hot chocolate in the city. It is definitely not your basic swiss miss drink. One small sip coats your entire mouth. Never too hot or too cold. It is amazing. It has a wonderful climate.
Great coffee, amazing pastries! I've had the baclava, and the cheese pies, both of which are really wonderful. Friendly service too. highly recommend!
Great coffee. Great selection of quick food and desserts.
Desserts here are fresh and delicious. Napoleon and Cheesecake Baklava were amazing.
Great place. Exceptional service! Mmm Napoleon!
A little bit of Greece in Charlotte NC. Great Coffee and Pastries... But,  better people that  own it. For all looking for a taste of Greece, make your way there.
The most friendly people work here! Always kind and helpful. The baked goods are wonderful as well. I'm never disappointed.
Homemade spinach pie and good coffee
Banana pudding & cheesecake baklava is amazing!!! Great place & very friendly staff.

Found my new favorite place :)
Good service, good food.
Very warm and comfortable.
I love this place. Great atmosphere and stuff. Coffee is perfect every time and sweets are great!!!!!!
If you're looking for an amazing atmosphere, hospitality, and great desserts look no further.
A real coffee house that has the right feel and Vibe. Any time of day you are welcome
Delicious desserts!
Such a great place!!!! Pastries here are delicious and coffee is perfection!
Great coffee and desseerts. Staff is very friendly too

I absolutely love this coffee shop! I was introduced to this spot by my Greek boyfriend. At first I got a chai tea latte which was great. Then one day he got their fredo cappuccino and o my goodness so good!

I now come every Tuesday on my day off of work and get a fredo cappuccino and a cheese pie! I wish they were open on Mondays so I can come for breakfast everyday off! I love this spot!
Amazing place, amazing people, excellent service. Used to meet up here with my friends every Friday. It's definitely worth to visit!
The coffee is delicious! I'm finding myself craving it every morning. Very friendly staff and the home made pastries look incredible.
Love the freddo cappucino
Doesn't look like much from the outside but stopped in for dessert and a coffee and everything was great. Even had comfortable couches rather than just bistro tables.
The best coffee and desserts in town. Come check it out!

One of the best coffee spots in Charlotte! Very friendly staff, yamm sweets and amazing coffee! Me and my friends just love meeting up there, for coffee, tea and sweets. Cream cluster pie is my favorite!!!
At last, real sweets not just sugar. I love this place.

Awsome coffee! !! And very delicious pastries! !
Is very comfortable and cozy and the owners are very friendly and caring
Hidden gem.  Best spinach pie!  Waiting for Jake to finish skateboarding, I walked here and it is really good coffee too!
Amazing place! Great desserts m.. Very friendly staff! And great coffee! Will definitely be back!

Stopped in on a Wednesday evening to try the coffee. Stayed for some chocolate cake. Loved it. The coffee was excellent (I ordered a cafe au lait, which isn't on the menu, but was one of the best I've had, certainly the best I've had on this side of town).
